   <head>To the Reader.</head>
   <l>I Cannot blame thee, if thou read'st not right,</l>
   <l>Or vnderstand'st not; for I know thy sight,</l>
   <l>ƲƲith weeping is imperfect, if not blind,</l>
   <l>And sorrow does (almost) distract thy mind.</l>
   <closer>
